>> TG:ID:API_ID:API_HASH:PHONE:AUTH. 
>> AUTH - cloud password
>> Example:
>> Have cloud password
TG:0:1881...:ajdkd829...:+1XXXXXXXXXX:123
>> Haven't cloud password
TG:1:1881...:ajdkd829...:+1XXXXXXXXXX:NONE
>> (You need to use fenrir TG --auth)

>> Actually, you can use identical API_HASH and API_ID,
>> But this is not recommended.

>> Moreover, if you have account sessions, you don't need to authenticate them,
>> so you can do this:

TG:2:1881...:ajdkd829...:NONE:NONE

>> But! You have to add session TG:2 (2.json) to .sessions
